##100% of the entry personnel declare their health condition in case of importation of foreign epidemic at Shanghai airport port

REPORTER: Fang Zhuoran

Shanghai customs will arrange a route away from ordinary passengers who have travelled and stayed in Korea, Italy, Iran, Japan and other countries within 14 days but have normal body temperature, and will concentrate them away from the airport, a 14-day home-based or intensive health observation was performed.

“

Shanghai customs will arrange a route away from ordinary passengers who have travelled and stayed in Korea, Italy, Iran, Japan and other countries within 14 days but have normal body temperature, and will concentrate them away from the airport, a 14-day home-based or intensive health observation was performed.

”

The port is the first point of entry into Shanghai, and Shanghai is the gateway for many people from abroad to other parts of the country. Therefore, the implementation of strict port prevention and control measures has become an important step in the prevention and control of epidemic situation, how to accurately and effectively prevent and control the importation of overseas epidemic situation has become a problem faced by Shanghai.

On the afternoon of March 3, Xu Wei, director of the Shanghai Municipal Government Information Office and spokesman for the municipal government, said that all Chinese and foreign personnel who had lived in key countries or regions in the 14 days prior to their entry into Shanghai, all patients were placed under 14-day home or intensive isolation health observation.

On March 4, the General Administration of Customs disclosed to the public that as of March 3,227 inbound passengers had fever symptoms, 63 suspected cases, and 5 nucleic acid-positive cases had been detected by the customs sampling, testing and screening transshipment department, there were four cases in Shanghai.

Subsequently, Zheng Jin, a spokesman for the Shanghai Municipal Health Commission, revealed that the four passengers who were handed over by Shanghai Customs and tested positive for nucleic acid were all confirmed as new coronary pneumonia, of which two were from Ningxia, China and one was from Qinghai, China, one case was from Gansu Province, China, both studying in Iran, both from Tehran, Iran, and arrived at the Shanghai Pudong International Airport in the evening of March 2 and early morning of March 3, respectively, after connecting via Bangkok, Thailand, after entering the customs, they were sent to the centralized isolation point for observation.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Shanghai Customs Officers Board flights from key regions. Photo: Shanghai Customs

In order to prevent the importation of foreign epidemic diseases, Shanghai Customs has carried out strict epidemic prevention and control work aimed at inbound passengers at Shanghai Pudong and Hongqiao Airports. Before each international flight departs and enters the arrival hall, it is necessary to enter the waiting area and complete the paper or electronic version of the health declaration card, which covers the countries and territories that have lived or travelled for 14 days, during this period, did you have any contact with patients with NCP, etc. .

After checking the passengers'health declaration cards, the staff will guide the passengers one by one into the temperature-measuring channel and conduct body temperature monitoring of the entry and exit persons by means of infrared thermometers, ear thermometers or thermometers, etc. , people with abnormal body temperature are re-tested with Mercury-in-glass thermometer (at least 2 times if necessary, and higher values are recorded) , and passengers with fever or respiratory symptoms are taken directly to the medical screening room for screening.

At the same time, the customs officer will take nasopharyngeal swabs and / or throat swabs, or take blood, deep-cough sputum and other samples if the person meets the epidemiological history and has fever and / or respiratory symptoms, to the lab for testing.

For passengers with normal body temperatures who have travelled and stayed in countries such as South Korea, Italy, Iran and Japan in 14 days, Shanghai Customs officials will arrange a route for them to leave the airport en masse away from ordinary passengers, a 14-day home or intensive health observation was carried out.

The identified confirmed cases, suspected cases, symptomatic people, close contacts of the "four categories of people" , all in accordance with the joint prevention and control mechanism to implement the transfer, isolation, observation and other preventive and control measures.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The Shanghai Customs officers shall carry out quarantine treatment on the aircraft suspected of being infected with the epidemic disease. Photo: Shanghai Customs

In addition to strict screening of incoming passengers, Shanghai Pudong and Hongqiao airports disinfect passengers'frequent use of facilities such as terminal toilets, mother-and-baby rooms, elevators, escalators and other densely populated areas every hour; Disinfection of manual and self-service check-in counters, on-the-spot interrogation counters, passenger seats and other facilities at least three times a day, and once every two hours during peak periods; real-time disinfection of the boarding corridors through which passengers must pass; Ensure that all flights are disinfected once.

At present, 276 toilets, mother-and-baby rooms and 243 rest areas in the terminal and satellite hall are continuously disinfected every day at Pudong Airport; the average daily disinfection area in Shanghai Hongqiao International Airport is more than 450,000 square meters, the airport group said, that's the equivalent of over 60 football fields.

In order to maintain air circulation in the public areas, the air conditioning has also increased the fresh air handling capacity in four terminals, a satellite hall and a traffic center, while ensuring a suitable temperature, open the side windows on the Glass Curtain Wall of the building in a timely manner to maintain good ventilation in the building. An in-depth disinfection of all air-conditioning filters and filters was completed at the airport, and more than 1,300 additional sets of UV disinfection lamps were activated for routine disinfection.
